HEADWORD: Turgescency
<hw>Tur*ges"cen*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>turgescence</ets>.
See <er>Turgescent</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of swelling, or
the state of being swollen, or turgescent.</def> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Empty magnificence or pompousness; inflation;
bombast; turgidity.</def> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turgescent</ent>⟦br⟧
